17/07/2006
BERLIN, Germany -- Army Chief-of-Staff General Wolfgang Schneiderhan reaffirmed his country's full support for Albania's NATO membership bid, during a meeting with his Albanian counterpart, General Lieutenant Pellumb Qazimi, in Berlin last week.
According to a statement from the Albanian Defence Ministry on Friday (14 July), talks between the two officials focused on the security situation in the Balkans and Europe, ongoing reforms in the Albanian Army, and German assistance.
(Albanian News - 15/07/06)
